summary: An ordinance accepting a perpetual easement from the Oregon- Washington Railroad & Navigation Company and the Oregon and Washington Railroad Company, corporations organized and existing under and by virtue of the laws of the State of Oregon, and qualified to do business in the State of Washington to the City of Seattle, a municipal corporation, dated October 16, 1912, for an overhead roadway or viaduct, over and across the following described property, situated in King County, State of Washington.
